      <intermediateExchange id="c7837c21-a360-5696-898c-75245c176d87" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="000075-78-5" amount="1.83202808621023" intermediateExchangeId="4135c4ce-e9ab-51d1-9c3e-592b616adb68" activityLinkId="562bc3d2-9b5c-58dc-a2a5-77e718211181">
        <name xml:lang="en">dimethyldichlorosilane</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
129.06054g/mol is the molar mass of dimethyldichlorosilane (C2H6Cl2Si). 
22246.362g/mol is the molar mass of polydimethylsiloxane (C600H1800O300Si300). 

The production of the silicone based antifoaming agent is modelled here as the production of polydimethylsiloxane. Polydimethylsiloxane is a polymer with n between 90 and 410 (FAO 2008). For this dataset the n assumed it n=300. Polydimethylsiloxane is produced from the reaction of dimethyldichlorosilane with water. Hydrochloric acid is produced during the reaction and is neutralized with potassium hydroxide.
Chemical reaction:
nSi(CH3)2Cl2 + (n+1)H2O -&gt; HO[-Si(CH3)2O-]nH + 2nHCl
where n=300</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="1.83202808621023" mu="0.6054235970352021" variance="0.0006" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.010025"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="3" temporalCorrelation="2" geographicalCorrelation="2" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="3"/>
        </uncertainty>
